-# ==================== HERO ====================
.hero.py-20.bg-base-200
  .hero-content.text-center
    .max-w-3xl
      %h1.text-5xl.font-bold About Us
      %p.py-6.text-lg.opacity-80
        Knowing Jesus, Making Jesus Known

-# ==================== OUR STORY ====================
.bg-base-100.py-16
  .max-w-7xl.mx-auto.px-4
    .grid.grid-cols-1.lg:grid-cols-2.gap-12.items-center
      .space-y-6
        %h2.text-4xl.font-bold Our Story
        %p.opacity-80
          Founded in 1992, Bethel Community Church exists to reach our community, teach believers
          biblical principles about loving God and neighbors, and send believers into the world to
          share their faith stories.
        %p.opacity-70
          Rooted in the Webster Groves community, we are committed to knowing Jesus and making
          Jesus known. Our doors are open to anyone seeking a place to grow in faith, build
          meaningful relationships, and discover their God-given purpose.
        %blockquote.border-l-4.border-primary.pl-4.italic.opacity-70
          "Therefore go and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father
          and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, and teaching them to obey everything I have
          commanded you."
          %span.block.mt-2.not-italic.font-semibold — Matthew 28:19-20
      %img.rounded-box.shadow-lg.w-full.h-80.object-cover{ src: "https://picsum.photos/seed/bethel-story/800/600", alt: "Our Story", loading: "lazy" }

-# ==================== OUR VALUES ====================
.bg-base-200.py-16
  .max-w-7xl.mx-auto.px-4
    %h2.text-4xl.font-bold.text-center.mb-12 Our Values
    .grid.grid-cols-1.md:grid-cols-2.lg:grid-cols-3.gap-6
      - [["Bible Authority & Inerrancy", "We believe the Bible is the authoritative Word of God and the standard for truth in all matters of faith and practice."], ["Christ-Centered Living", "We are committed to wholehearted devotion to God through Christ-centered living in every area of life."], ["Dependence on God & Prayer", "We rely on God across all areas of life, with individual and corporate prayer as essential to our ministry."], ["Equipping Believers for Ministry", "We equip believers for ministry based on their spiritual gifts, empowering each person to serve in their calling."], ["Loving Relationships", "We build loving relationships marked by acceptance and forgiveness, reflecting the love of Christ to one another."], ["Contemporary Worship", "We express our love for God through vibrant and heartfelt contemporary worship."], ["Small Group Formation", "We encourage small group participation for spiritual development, accountability, and authentic community."], ["Family & Youth Ministry", "We strengthen families through dedicated youth, children's, and young adult programs."], ["Missions Focus", "We support missionary work through financial giving, intercession, and direct participation in spreading the gospel."], ["Empowered Leadership", "We empower leaders throughout the congregation to serve and lead with excellence."]].each do |title, description|
        .card.bg-base-100.shadow-lg
          .card-body
            %h3.card-title= title
            %p.opacity-70= description

-# ==================== WHAT WE BELIEVE ====================
.bg-base-100.py-16
  .max-w-7xl.mx-auto.px-4
    %h2.text-4xl.font-bold.text-center.mb-12 What We Believe
    .max-w-3xl.mx-auto.space-y-2

      .collapse.collapse-arrow.bg-base-200.shadow
        %input{ type: "radio", name: "beliefs-accordion", checked: true }
        .collapse-title.font-semibold
          The Holy Scriptures
          %span.text-sm.font-normal.opacity-60.ml-2 (1 Thess. 2:13; 2 Tim. 3:16)
        .collapse-content
          %p
            We believe the Bible is the inspired Word of God, is inerrant in the original writings,
            and is our sole authority for faith and practice.

      .collapse.collapse-arrow.bg-base-200.shadow
        %input{ type: "radio", name: "beliefs-accordion" }
        .collapse-title.font-semibold
          The Trinity
          %span.text-sm.font-normal.opacity-60.ml-2 (Mark 12:29; John 4:24; Matt. 3:16-17; Matt. 28:19; 2 Cor. 13:14)
        .collapse-content
          %p
            We believe there is only one true and living God who exists in three eternal and co-equal
            persons: the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit.

      .collapse.collapse-arrow.bg-base-200.shadow
        %input{ type: "radio", name: "beliefs-accordion" }
        .collapse-title.font-semibold
          God the Father
          %span.text-sm.font-normal.opacity-60.ml-2 (Rev. 15:4; John 4:24; 1 Chron. 29:11-12; Jer. 31:3; Mal. 3:6)
        .collapse-content
          %p
            We believe the Father is the first person of the Trinity; is Spirit, and is the ultimate
            expression of perfection and holiness. He is exalted as head above all, eternal, immutable,
            omniscient, and omnipotent.

      .collapse.collapse-arrow.bg-base-200.shadow
        %input{ type: "radio", name: "beliefs-accordion" }
        .collapse-title.font-semibold
          Jesus Christ
          %span.text-sm.font-normal.opacity-60.ml-2 (John 1:18, 8:58; Matt. 1:23; Col. 1:15-17; 1 Tim. 1:15, 3:16; 1 Peter 2:24; 1 Thess. 4:13-18)
        .collapse-content
          %p
            We believe Jesus Christ is the pre-existent Son of God who became man to reveal God and
            redeem man. He was born of the Virgin Mary supernaturally, lived sinlessly, died sacrificially,
            rose bodily, ascended to the Father's right hand, and will return to reign.

      .collapse.collapse-arrow.bg-base-200.shadow
        %input{ type: "radio", name: "beliefs-accordion" }
        .collapse-title.font-semibold
          The Holy Spirit
          %span.text-sm.font-normal.opacity-60.ml-2 (Acts 5:3-4; John 16:7-11,13; Titus 3:5; Eph. 1:13; 1 Cor. 6:19, 12:13-14)
        .collapse-content
          %p
            We believe the Holy Spirit is the third Person of the Trinity who convicts the world of sin,
            righteousness, and judgment. He creates anew, seals and indwells believers, gives spiritual
            gifts, and instructs, guides, comforts, and empowers the believer.

      .collapse.collapse-arrow.bg-base-200.shadow
        %input{ type: "radio", name: "beliefs-accordion" }
        .collapse-title.font-semibold
          Creation
          %span.text-sm.font-normal.opacity-60.ml-2 (Gen. 2:4; Prov. 16:4; Acts 17:24; Col. 1:17)
        .collapse-content
          %p
            We believe the Triune God created the heavens and the earth out of nothing. All living things
            came into being by the direct creative act of God.

      .collapse.collapse-arrow.bg-base-200.shadow
        %input{ type: "radio", name: "beliefs-accordion" }
        .collapse-title.font-semibold
          Humanity
          %span.text-sm.font-normal.opacity-60.ml-2 (Gen. 1:26-27; Rom. 3:10, 23; Eph. 2:1-3; 4:18)
        .collapse-content
          %p
            We believe man was created in the image and likeness of God in innocence, distinct in gender.
            Through disobedience, man fell and lost fellowship with God. The entire human race has inherited
            a corrupt nature which is essentially evil and unable to please God apart from His grace.

      .collapse.collapse-arrow.bg-base-200.shadow
        %input{ type: "radio", name: "beliefs-accordion" }
        .collapse-title.font-semibold
          Salvation
          %span.text-sm.font-normal.opacity-60.ml-2 (1 Pet. 1:18-19; 2 Cor. 5:21; Eph. 2:8-9; Rom. 5:1; Titus 3:5; John 6:35-40)
        .collapse-content
          %p
            We believe salvation is provided only through the blood of Jesus Christ which He shed on
            the cross. It cannot be earned through works but requires personal faith in Christ as
            substitute. At salvation, sins are forgiven, God's righteousness is credited, and the
            believer is declared "not guilty." Salvation is the complete and permanent possession of
            every believer.

      .collapse.collapse-arrow.bg-base-200.shadow
        %input{ type: "radio", name: "beliefs-accordion" }
        .collapse-title.font-semibold
          The Church
          %span.text-sm.font-normal.opacity-60.ml-2 (1 Cor. 12:12-27; Matt. 28:19-20; Eph. 5:32; Heb. 13:17)
        .collapse-content
          %p
            We believe the Church, referred to as the Body and Bride of Christ, is a unique organism
            composed of all individuals who have placed faith in Christ. The local church expresses the
            universal Church with the dual purpose of edification of believers and the evangelization of
            the lost. Water baptism by immersion is a voluntary public profession, not essential to salvation.

      .collapse.collapse-arrow.bg-base-200.shadow
        %input{ type: "radio", name: "beliefs-accordion" }
        .collapse-title.font-semibold
          Marriage
          %span.text-sm.font-normal.opacity-60.ml-2 (Matt. 19:3-6; Eph. 5:21-33)
        .collapse-content
          %p
            We believe in the biblical definition of marriage as the intimate and complementary union
            between a man and a woman where the two become one flesh.

      .collapse.collapse-arrow.bg-base-200.shadow
        %input{ type: "radio", name: "beliefs-accordion" }
        .collapse-title.font-semibold
          End Times
          %span.text-sm.font-normal.opacity-60.ml-2 (John 14:3; 1 Thess. 4:13-18; Matt. 24:21-31; Rev. 20-22)
        .collapse-content
          %p
            We believe the next event in God's prophetic calendar is the Rapture of the Church. A
            seven-year Tribulation follows, after which Christ returns in power and glory to rule
            sovereignly for a thousand years. The redeemed will exist in an eternal state of joy and
            bliss in the new heavens and new earth.

-# ==================== LEADERSHIP ====================
- leaders = [["David Baumgartner", "Elder", "bethel-leader1"], ["John Kloeppel", "Elder", "bethel-leader2"], ["Tom Grass", "Elder", "bethel-leader3"], ["Kevin Stiles", "Elder", "bethel-leader4"], ["Jeff Smith", "Elder", "bethel-leader5"], ["Ted Tash", "Deacon", "bethel-leader6"], ["David Vinyard", "Deacon", "bethel-leader7"], ["Kent Stiles", "Deacon", "bethel-leader8"], ["Brad Kloeppel", "Deacon", "bethel-leader9"]]
.bg-base-200.py-16
  .max-w-7xl.mx-auto.px-4
    %h2.text-4xl.font-bold.text-center.mb-12 Leadership
    .carousel.carousel-center.gap-6.w-full.py-4
      - leaders.each_with_index do |(name, role, seed), index|
        - modal_id = "leader_modal_#{index}"
        .carousel-item
          .card.bg-base-100.shadow-lg.cursor-pointer.hover:shadow-xl.transition-shadow.w-64{ onclick: "#{modal_id}.showModal()" }
            %figure
              %img.h-64.w-full.object-cover{ src: "https://picsum.photos/seed/#{seed}/400/500", alt: name, loading: "lazy" }
            .card-body.items-center.text-center
              %h3.card-title= name
              %p.opacity-70= role
    -# Leadership modals
    - bios = { "David Baumgartner" => ["David and Mary Ellen were born and raised in St. Louis, Missouri. They both came to Christ during the \"Jesus Movement\" in the 70's and, after living many years in Colorado and Kansas, returned home to St. Louis in 1995. They celebrated their 40th wedding anniversary in January of 2017, and currently have two grown children and four grandchildren.", "David was in full-time ministry at Bethel from 1999 until his retirement in 2024. He serves as an elder and completed a Masters Degree in Divinity from Covenant Theological Seminary in 2010. He continues to serve in the music and speaking ministry."] }
    - leaders.each_with_index do |(name, role, seed), index|
      - modal_id = "leader_modal_#{index}"
      %dialog.modal{ id: modal_id }
        .modal-box.max-w-2xl
          %div.flex.justify-between.items-center.mb-4
            %h3.text-2xl.font-bold= name
            %form{ method: "dialog" }
              %button.btn.btn-sm.btn-circle.btn-ghost ✕
          %p.text-sm.opacity-60.mb-4= role
          - if bios[name]
            - bios[name].each do |paragraph|
              %p.opacity-80.mt-4= paragraph
          - else
            %p.opacity-80 Bio coming soon.
        %form.modal-backdrop{ method: "dialog" }
          %button close

-# ==================== VISIT CTA ====================
.bg-primary.text-primary-content.py-16
  .max-w-7xl.mx-auto.px-4.text-center
    %h2.text-4xl.font-bold.mb-4 Come Visit Us
    %p.text-lg.opacity-90.mb-8
      We'd love to meet you and your family. Join us for worship and experience the warm,
      welcoming community at Bethel. No matter where you are on your faith journey, there's
      a place for you here.
    = link_to 'Plan Your Visit', root_path(anchor: 'service-times'), class: 'btn btn-secondary btn-lg'
